      • startTransactionFlow

        public void startTransactionFlow(java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> data)
        Start the transaction with specified CheckCardMode (Swipe/Insert/Tap). The Controller will take control and go through all the EMV process.

        Callback Functions:
        BaseCardController.onCardInteractionDetecting(CheckCardMode) ,

        Parameters:
        data - hashtable key and values.

        EMV_OPTION : Indicate whether to force transaction go online, see EmvOption enumeration.
        TRANSACTIONTYPE : Indicate the type of financial transaction, see TransactionType enumeration.
        BaseCardController.CHKCRD_MODE : Indicate which check card mode to use, see CheckCardMode enumeration.
        EMV_ISPEDDLLDISABLE : Indicate whether Offline PIN is handle by PEDDLL.
        BaseCardController.CHKCRD_TIMEOUT : Indicate the check card timeout, in second.
        EMV_PINTIMEOUT : Indicate the pin entry timeout, in second.
        EMV_SETAMTTIMEOUT : Indicate the set amount timeout, in second
        EMV_SELAPPTIMEOUT : Indicate the select application timeout, in second.
        EMV_ONLTIMEOUT : Indicate the online process timeout, in second.
        EMV_FNLCONFRIMTIMEOUT : Indicate the final confirm timeout, in second.
        EMV_TXNNO: Indicate the transaction number(Tag 9F41)
        EMV_ISCLFINALCONFIRMATIONENABLE : Indicate whether enable finalConfirmation for contactless transaction
        EMV_SUPPORT_UPIWORLDWIDE : Indicate whether enable UPI worldwide checking (default false, HK and MACAU)
        AMOUNT : Transaction Amount.
        CASHBACKAMOUNT : Cashback Amount
        CURRENCYCODE : 3-digits transaction currency code (e.g. "344" for HKD).
        GET_DATA_TAG_LIST : String Data Tag List to be retrieve (e.g."DF20DF21DF22DF23DF25DF50DF60").
        CUSTOM_TLV : String TLV DATA.

      • selectAID

        public void selectAID(int index)
        Set the customer selected application index.

        An chip card may support multiple payment applications. The list of Applications IDs supported by the card and device is returned in onRequestSelectApplication(ArrayList) The App should prompt the customer select an application to continue the transaction.

        Parameters:
        index - The index of the application selected.

      • sendOnlineProcessingData

        public void sendOnlineProcessingData(java.lang.String tlv)
        Send back the online process result to the card in response to onOnlineProcessRequested. To terminate the transaction, send null or empty string as result.
        Parameters:
        tlv - A set of transaction results in Tag-Length-Value format.

      • getEmvCardData

        public void getEmvCardData()
        Get the card data from EMV chip card. This command is not used in EMV transaction process. To cancel the check card process, call abortDetection() at BaseCardController.onCardInteractionDetecting(CheckCardMode).

        Callback :
        BaseCardController.onCardInteractionDetecting(CheckCardMode),
        BaseCardController.onCardInteractionDetected(CheckCardResult, Hashtable),
        TransactionFlowController.TransactionFlowDelegate.onEmvCardDataReceived(boolean, String).
